# Settings — Design Locked

The settings section design is **complete**. Do not change layout, styling, structure, or UX unless the user explicitly asks.

## Do not change without confirmation

- `components/settings/*` (SettingsModal, ProfileTab, PasswordTab, settingsTabs)
- Settings-related CSS in `index.css` (`.settings-*`, `.settings-shell-card`)
- `context/SettingsContext.jsx`
- `components/common/Modal.jsx` when used for settings

## Allowed without asking

- Bug fixes that restore intended behavior (broken upload, API errors, validation)
- New fields or tabs **only when the user explicitly requests them**

## Before any settings design tweak

Ask the user or wait for explicit approval — includes spacing, colors, opacity, header heights, tab layout, form layout, and modal width.
